macro.title: Pending Home Sales Slip As Would-Be Buyers Wait For Lower Rates and Economic Clarity
macro.what: The homes that do sell are taking a long time to find buyers, who are wary of high housing costs and economic instability
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

macro.title: Redfin Economists’ Weekly Take: Fresh Government Data Could Bring Mortgage Rate Volatility
macro.what: This Week In A Nutshell The government shutdown looks likely to end this week, which means a flurry of fresh economic data over the next month or so could bring mortgage-rate volatility as investors reprice the odds of future rate cuts
